      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Execution of Gary Graham</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Oren M Spiegler letter says liberals who protest execution of Gary Graham in Texas should think about his victims (June 23 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''With Bush Assent, Inmate Is Executed'' (front page, June 23):</p>
        <p>I wonder if the liberals who protested emotionally on behalf of Gary Graham ever took a moment to think about the victims of his brutal crimes.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''With Bush Assent, Inmate Is Executed'' (front page, June 23):</p>
        <p>I wonder if the liberals who protested emotionally on behalf of Gary Graham ever took a moment to think about the victims of his brutal crimes.</p>
        <p>Would the righteous indignation within them ever extend to mobilizing to denounce the acts of individuals like him, who seek to destroy our society?</p>
        <p>Would they become as overcome with emotion as they are over his death if they heard stories of the innocent victims of his crimes?</p>
        <p>Mr. Graham suffered a far more merciful, peaceful death than he meted out. The travesty is that almost two decades passed before justice was done.</p>
        <p>OREN M. SPIEGLER  Pittsburgh, June 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
